text: Kaipkulovo () is a rural locality (a village) in Novobayramgulovsky Selsoviet, Uchalinsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 107 as of 2010. There are 4 streets. == Geography == It is located 63 km from Uchaly, 2 km from Uchaly. == References == Category:Rural localities in Uchalinsky District
title: Kaipkulovo
